{
  "texts": [
    "The FF network has twice as many pre-trained parameters as compared to MHA (see Table II).",
    "Hence, the FF network is divided into two stages given that the throughput of the pipelined system is constrained by its slowest component.",
    "Overall, the intra-layer pipeline consists of four stages with ReRAM utilized in three of these stages and systolic array utilized in the remaining stage.",
    "We allocate resources accordingly in the ratio of 3:1 among ReRAM and systolic array cores.",
    "The 3D system under consideration is structured with four planar tiers, each with size 10 mm x 10mm."
  ]
}